174
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:23,637
Influencer?

175
00:14:24,830 --> 00:14:30,421
These days, the advertising market prefers influencers over celebrities.

176
00:14:30,421 --> 00:14:37,957
Influencers with great followings use their influence to sell many things and make a profit.

177
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:42,765
Somebody said something like this.

178
00:14:42,765 --> 00:14:49,460
Uber doesn't have any cars, and Airbnb doesn't own any houses.

179
00:14:49,460 --> 00:14:54,300
But still, they are ranked number one in their respective areas.

180
00:14:54,300 --> 00:15:01,200
So are you saying that we should build a market platform for influencers?

181
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,690
Well, wait─

182
00:15:02,690 --> 00:15:05,280
I think it's great.

183
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:06,780
Yes, I agree.

184
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:13,350
I also look at influencers I like on social media to see what they are up to.

185
00:15:13,355 --> 00:15:17,003
And it's a platform where they are collectively concentrated?

186
00:15:17,828 --> 00:15:19,630
I think it will work.

187
00:15:19,630 --> 00:15:26,980
You can find new influencers and get every information like their clothing and lipsticks.

188
00:15:26,980 --> 00:15:31,000
