00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:53,660
♫ Uh, maybe he's acting like he doesn't know ♫

251
00:19:53,660 --> 00:19:57,290
♫ But at least ♫

252
00:19:57,290 --> 00:20:00,310
♫ I don't mind knowing him alone ♫

253
00:20:00,310 --> 00:20:02,460
♫ Strangely, I don't dislike that ♫

254
00:20:02,460 --> 00:20:07,240
[Work hard and repay with good results. - Your team leader]

255
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:10,470
♫ Just like you, just like you ♫

256
00:20:10,470 --> 00:20:13,210
♫ The world looks so beautiful ♫

257
00:20:13,210 --> 00:20:17,580
How can a person like him become such a sucker whenever he meets the guy from unit 303?

258
00:20:17,580 --> 00:20:21,270
♫ The vibe is always so good ♫

259
00:20:25,030 --> 00:20:27,340
Why is he not coming?

260
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:42,070
I'm sorry! I was grabbing one more document.

261
00:20:42,070 --> 00:20:43,800
Seriously...

262
00:20:47,410 --> 00:20:51,480
- Are you ready?
- Yes! I'm ready.

263
00:20:57,130 --> 00:21:01,340
Excuse me? What do you mean, we can't have a meeting?

264
00:21:01,340 --> 00:21:04,880
We haven't heard anything about you coming today.

265
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:08,270
What are you talking about right now?

266
00:21:08,270 --> 00:21:13,790
Also, how can you come during lunch break?

267
00:21:13,790 --> 00:21:17,840
This is PR Team 1. Yes?

268
00:21:19,750 --> 00:21:22,680
Ah, okay.

269
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:24,980
I get it.

270
00:21:27,590 --> 00:21:29,440
I'm so sorry about that.

271
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:32,590
The head of the department just checked and told me you are right.

272
00:21:32,590 --> 00:21:34,700
I think he got confused with the dates.

273
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:37,980
He's on a business trip, so he won't be back until next week.

274
00:21:50,010 --> 00:21:52,440
You are going to make the ground sink.

275
00:21:55,050 --> 00:21:57,910
Why are you so disappointed?

276
00:22:02,750 --> 00:22:06,940
Since it became like this, shall we go for a meal?

277
00:22:07,610 --> 00:22:10,290
No, it's okay. Let's just go back to the office.

278
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:15,320
Let's go.

279
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:17,070
Where to?

280
00:22:17,070 --> 00:22:20,030
- Don't say any more, and just follow me.
- What?

281
00:22:33,670 --> 00:22:36,260
Didn't you say, let's go for a meal?

282
00:22:36,260 --> 00:22:38,630
There are a lot of restaurants around here as well.

283
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:43,580
You didn't have to be this dramatic.

284
00:22:43,580 --> 00:22:46,670
Wow, you talk a lot.

285
00:22:46,670 --> 00:22:48,200
Get out of the car.

286
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:57,530
What's the deal with him?

287
00:23:04,990 --> 00:23:08,610
You said it was too dramatic.

288
00:23:11,460 --> 00:23:17,130
♫  Stay in my dreams, let's be together  ♫

289
00:23:17,130 --> 00:23:18,970
♫ If you appear in my dream today too, ♫

290
00:23:18,970 --> 00:23:22,625
Where did the bitter-faced Seo Jae Yun go?

291
00:23:24,140 --> 00:23:28,972
This is my first time seeing such a beautiful ocean.

292
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:34,070
♫ Every moment with you, all the time we spent together ♫

293
00:23:34,070 --> 00:23:41,560
♫ When I think about them, I feel overwhelmed; dreaming of you every day ♫

294
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:50,840
Do you want to drink something?

295
00:23:51,530 --> 00:23:55,150
Well, I think I'm okay.

296
00:23:55,150 --> 00:23:57,000
Let's just drink something.

297
00:23:57,000 --> 00:24:05,190
♫ I'll hold you tight, dreaming of you every day  ♫

298
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:15,299
If you come to the beach, you got to have soju with raw fish.

299
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:21,590
During working hours? Alcohol?

300
00:24:24,130 --> 00:24:27,040
If you don't want it, just give it to me.

301
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:29,080
When did I say I won't drink it?

302
00:24:40,810 --> 00:24:42,590
Thank you.

303
00:24:43,260 --> 00:24:45,080
Out of the blue?

304
00:24:45,080 --> 00:24:49,660
I know you brought me to the beach because I was feeling down.

305
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:54,290
That's what I've been saying, but for the sake of our team─

306
00:24:54,290 --> 00:24:55,670
I know that.

307
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:58,690
And I thank you for that.

308
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:04,150
Thanks to you, I really feel better.

309
00:25:04,150 --> 00:25:10,508
If it weren't for you, I might have just drunk beer alone in my room.

310
00:25:20,750 --> 00:25:24,078
I have a question for you.

311
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:28,380
Why are you working so hard?

312
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:33,710
What's wrong with working hard?

313
00:25:33,710 --> 00:25:38,515
I wondered why someone who owns a building works under other people.

314
00:25:39,122 --> 00:25:43,121
You can just collect rent and live comfortably, can't you?

315
00:25:44,010 --> 00:25:47,870
I know a lot of people who live comfortably like that.

316
00:25:50,730 --> 00:25:53,310
I still have a lot of mortgages left.

317
00:25:53,310 --> 00:25:57,350
As you know, Geumnam pays the best.

318
00:25:59,560 --> 00:26:05,450
But that's not the only reason.

319
00:26:05,450 --> 00:26:10,013
This kind of story needs some alcohol to be talked about.

320
00:26:11,260 --> 00:26:14,790
Are you saying that because I didn't buy you a drink?

321
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:32,216
My family went bankrupt big time once.

322
00:26:37,550 --> 00:26:42,002
My father was having a boiler business, and he blew it.

323
00:26:44,930 --> 00:26:48,740
That's when I learned that the red stickers I only saw in TV shows actually exist.

324
00:26:48,740 --> 00:26:51,230
You haven't seen those in real life, have you?

325
00:26:51,230 --> 00:26:54,080
It's really daunting.

326
00:26:56,460 --> 00:27:03,167
My father worked really hard day and night to develop the technology.

327
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:10,470
But one day, the same exact product came out in the TV ads.

328
00:27:10,470 --> 00:27:16,010
It turned out that another company copied my father's technology.

329
00:27:18,420 --> 00:27:21,950
And it all started from there. A sad tenant's life has begun.

330
00:27:21,950 --> 00:27:24,440
It's all in the past now.

331
00:27:28,550 --> 00:27:31,530
But did he not do anything about it?

332
00:27:31,530 --> 00:27:36,960
We couldn't do anything because my father didn't even put out a tiny ad in a newspaper.

333
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:43,120
But the other company did everything they could, like TV commercials and home shopping.

334
00:27:43,120 --> 00:27:45,873
So when we got ourselves together,

335
00:27:45,873 --> 00:27:50,509
it was my father who copied them, not the other way around.

336
00:27:53,810 --> 00:27:57,960
So since then, I have wanted to know.

337
00:27:57,960 --> 00:28:03,347
I wondered what my father, who only worked hard, should have done.

338
00:28:06,500 --> 00:28:09,800
That's why I joined this company. I came here to learn.

339
00:28:09,800 --> 00:28:11,520
To learn?

340
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:12,992
Yes.

341
00:28:14,430 --> 00:28:17,680
I suddenly feel a great amount of responsibility.

342
00:28:19,530 --> 00:28:23,467
I already learned something from you.

343
00:28:24,890 --> 00:28:27,340
I didn't show you anything.

344
00:28:28,070 --> 00:28:30,410
You told me this before.

345
00:28:30,410 --> 00:28:36,250
Don't lose the opportunity you got, no matter what. Hold on to it tightly.

346
00:28:38,090 --> 00:28:41,790
Honestly, I got scared at first.

347
00:28:41,790 --> 00:28:48,952
But after hearing what you said, I thought about why I wanted to do this work once again.

348
00:28:50,895 --> 00:28:55,491
But of course, I have to wait ten days to do so.

349
00:28:59,050 --> 00:29:00,870
I should have bought some alcoholic drinks.

350
00:29:00,870 --> 00:29:04,320
I know. It's too bad.

351
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:09,300
What's bad is your uncontrollable behavior when you get drunk.

352
00:29:09,300 --> 00:29:10,970
- My drunken behavior?
- Yes.

353
00:29:10,970 --> 00:29:13,330
- I don't have any specific behavior when I get drunk.
- What?

354
00:29:13,330 --> 00:29:17,560
Do you think you don't have one? Oh, my...

355
00:29:17,560 --> 00:29:21,190
♫ Whenever it is, ♫

356
00:29:21,190 --> 00:29:24,010
♫ I can tell how lonely you would be alone ♫

357
00:29:24,012 --> 00:29:29,868
Do you remember that day?

358
00:29:31,010 --> 00:29:35,595
If the day you are thinking of is the day I'm thinking of, then yes.

359
00:29:39,910 --> 00:29:41,610
Jade mats?

360
00:29:41,610 --> 00:29:46,002
And your twelve insurances and massage chairs.

361
00:29:46,880 --> 00:29:51,280
Then... What about Seung Seok?

362
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:54,750
Oh, your fiancé?

363
00:29:56,210 --> 00:29:59,000
You said you don't remember when you drink!

364
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:04,800
Right, but somehow I remember every detail of that day.

365
00:30:05,430 --> 00:30:08,550
- Did you lie to me?
- No.

366
00:30:09,340 --> 00:30:12,590
Technically, it wasn't a lie.

367
00:30:13,564 --> 00:30:18,276
I really don't remember what happened when I drank, but somehow I do remember that day.

368
00:30:24,620 --> 00:30:27,620
Let's do cheers. It's all in the past.

369
00:30:27,620 --> 00:30:31,670
I kept it secret for the past week, in case you are concerned about it.

370
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:36,420
- Let's do cheers. My arm is about to fall off!
- It's embarrassing!

371
00:30:36,420 --> 00:30:39,310
Don't talk to me. I'm embarrassed.

372
00:30:40,610 --> 00:30:42,056
Cheers.

373
00:30:51,200 --> 00:30:55,640
But, by the way.

374
00:30:55,640 --> 00:31:01,830
Should I tell him to stop being such a pushover? Or am I being too nosy?

375
00:31:01,830 --> 00:31:04,980
- But what?
- It's nothing.

376
00:31:04,980 --> 00:31:11,167
You always stop talking in the middle of the sentence. Oh, well!

377
00:31:11,970 --> 00:31:15,182
Let's just go now. We'll get caught in the traffic.

378
00:31:15,870 --> 00:31:23,280
♫ If my existence gives you strength and comfort, ♫

379
00:31:23,280 --> 00:31:25,620
When am I going to come here again?

380
00:31:25,620 --> 00:31:30,860
♫ That is enough ♫

381
00:31:30,860 --> 00:31:36,380
♫ I'll be your light, your tree, ♫

382
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:38,060
It's beautiful.

383
00:31:38,060 --> 00:31:41,460
♫ A resting place in great shade ♫

384
00:31:41,460 --> 00:31:47,980
♫ For you to rest without thinking, ♫

385
00:31:47,980 --> 00:31:49,750
I'm talking about the ocean.

386
00:32:01,690 --> 00:32:08,720
♫ Oh, look around, there is nothing easy in this world ♫

387
00:32:08,720 --> 00:32:15,270
♫ Uh, but it seems that my heart is at ease ♫

388
00:32:16,150 --> 00:32:22,670
♫ Sometimes I don't know why you act so edgy ♫

389
00:32:22,670 --> 00:32:29,140
♫ And it's so strange that I still don't hate that ♫

390
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:30,980
Seo Jae Yun!

391
00:32:30,980 --> 00:32:34,680
He's earned scholarships all through college.

392
00:32:34,680 --> 00:32:36,880
I have a feeling.

393
00:32:36,880 --> 00:32:42,240
I have a sixth sense kind of feeling that this guy will make my salary rise dramatically.

394
00:32:42,240 --> 00:32:45,790
I thought it was odd since he's quite young to be a team leader.

395
00:32:45,790 --> 00:32:49,220
But I figured he was such a talented person after hearing about him.

396
00:32:49,220 --> 00:32:53,720
Manager Choi and Assistant Manager Kim, you two do project planning and system development.

397
00:32:53,720 --> 00:33:01,320
And Seo Jae Yun, you and I will contact the influencers until the market opens.

398
00:33:01,320 --> 00:33:05,654
Jae Yun! I'm sorry to ask you such a favor at the last minute.

399
00:33:05,654 --> 00:33:07,068
What's going on?

